FTSE 100 Benchmark Declines; GlaxoSmithKline, HSBC, Shell Drop in London

-- B y   J a s o n   C a r e y
-- 
2011-05-17T12:43:01Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-17/ftse-100-benchmark-declines-glaxosmithkline-hsbc-shell-drop-in-london.html
U.K. stocks fell for a fifth day, led
 by  GlaxoSmithKline Plc (GSK) ,  HSBC Holdings Plc (HSBA)  and  Royal Dutch Shell
Plc. (RDSA)   The benchmark FTSE 100 Index dropped 0.4 percent to
5,898.53 at 1:39 p.m. in London.  Glaxo slipped 1.9 percent to 1,322 pence, HSBC fell 0.6
percent to 638.7 pence and Shell sank 0.9 percent to 2,121.5
pence.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Jason Carey at 
 jcarey3@bloomberg.net  